 century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Tatton was born about 1297, in Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Alice de WITHENSHAW."},"et":{"about 1297–Deceased":"umbes 1297–Surnud","1297–Female":"1297–Surnud","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1297–Male":"1297–Surnud","1348":"1348","1297":"1297","about 1297":"umbes 1297","1329":"1329","Of Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1297–Deceased":"noin 1297–Kuollut","1297–Female":"1297–Kuollut","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1297–Male":"1297–Kuollut","1348":"1348","1297":"1297","about 1297":"noin 1297","1329":"1329","Of Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1297–Deceased":"environ 1297–Décédé","1297–Female":"1297–Décédée","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1297–Male":"1297–Décédé","1348":"1348","1297":"1297","about 1297":"environ 1297","1329":"1329","Of Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert de Tatton est né environ 1297, à Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Alice de WITHENSHAW."},"de":{"about 1297–Deceased":"um 1297–Verstorben","1297–Female":"1297–Verstorben","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1297–Male":"1297–Verstorben","1348":"1348","1297":"1297","about 1297":"um 1297","1329":"1329","Of Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert de Tatton wurde um 1297 in Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Engla